intro: Cyclandrophora nannodes, commonly known as the small-leafed cyclandrophora, is a flowering plant native to the tropical regions of Southeast Asia. It belongs to the family Araliaceae and is characterized by its compact growth habit and palmate leaves. The plant produces small, greenish-white flowers that are clustered in umbels, which are typically borne on short peduncles. Cyclandrophora nannodes is often found in shaded, moist environments such as forest understories and rocky crevices. Its botanical features make it an interesting subject for horticultural study and conservation efforts.
